            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Further to @Prospero&apos;s comment above: you can absolutely send files via POST without using &lt;code&gt;multipart/form-data&lt;/code&gt;. What you &lt;i&gt;can&apos;t&lt;/i&gt; do is do that using an ordinary HTML form submission, without JavaScript. Setting a form to use &lt;code&gt;multipart/form-data&lt;/code&gt; is the only mechanism that &lt;i&gt;HTML&lt;/i&gt; provides to let you POST files without using JavaScript. I feel like this isn&apos;t clear enough in the answer, and that a naive reader might think that the inability to send files without &lt;code&gt;multipart/form-data&lt;/code&gt; is a limitation of &lt;i&gt;HTTP&lt;/i&gt;; that&apos;s not the case.&lt;/span&gt;

