            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;The stuff about security after the most recent edit is all irrelevant to the question of what &lt;code&gt;enctype&lt;/code&gt;s do. I know it&apos;s literally from the &lt;code&gt;multipart/form-data&lt;/code&gt; RFC, but nonetheless it&apos;s an arbitrary dump of security considerations about submitting forms that are entirely orthogonal to whether data is sent as &lt;code&gt;application/x-www-form-urlencoded&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;multipart/form-data&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

